                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 7357/368.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Dodge</persName> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.—Extract.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Tegucigalpa</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1908-09-07">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 7, 1908</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Mr. Dodge acknowledges department’s telegram of September 5, and reports having
                    arranged with the minister for foreign affairs that the decree will be
                    published, omitting the word “unjustifiable.” States that the matter is settled,
                    and that he proposes to return to San Salvador September 11.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
